  "prompt": "What is act exam?",
  "response": "The ACT (American College Testing) exam is a standardized test used for college admissions in the United States. It is intended to measure a high school student's academic readiness for college. The ACT assesses four main areas:\n\n1. **English**: This section tests grammar, punctuation, sentence structure, and rhetorical skills.\n2. **Mathematics**: This section includes topics such as algebra, geometry, and trigonometry.\n3. **Reading**: This section evaluates reading comprehension.\n4. **Science**: This section assesses scientific reasoning skills and interpretation of data.\n\nThere is also an optional Writing (essay) section that tests writing skills. The ACT is scored on a scale of 1 to 36 for each of the four main sections, and the composite score is the average of these four scores. The optional Writing section is scored separately. The test is widely accepted by colleges and universities in the United States as part of the admissions process.",
